{
  "texts": [
    "In Section 4.1.1, we presented the different eye tracker frequencies.",
    "The majority of experiments were conducted with lower frequency eye trackers, e.g., 60 Hz.",
    "According to the discussion in Section 5.3, lower frequency eye trackers could lead to sampling errors in the recordings, which was not discussed or reported by publications.",
    "In addition, we found out that for saccade-based features, it is recommended to use an eye tracker with 120 to 200 Hz, which was also not discussed by multiple publications that used lower frequencies.",
    "The usage of complex machine learning algorithms, especially with large datasets, and cross-validation (Section 4.2.2) can take a lot of resources to train and optimize the model."
  ]
}